{
  "text": "In other words, a change in the consumption of oil and gas through backup generators does not affect the variables of TNTPR t and CU t . This can be supported by the fact that backup generators are used only when an electricity shortage occurs, as the electricity generated by backup generators is more costly for users than the grid electricity distributed from power plants [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The definitions of the variables and the corresponding units of measurement used in the analysis are summarized in table 2.",
